title: pythonw testscript.py produces FileNotFoundError: File .../DeepLabCut/examples/TEST-Alex-2021-02-04/labeled-data/reachingvideo1short/machinelabels-iter0.h5 does not exist
body: OS: macOS Catalina 10.15.6 DeepLabCut Version: DeepLabCut 2.1.10 Anaconda env used: DLC-CPU **Describe the problem** I've been trying to run testscript.py located in DeepLabCut/examples. I have been following the video located [here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IOWtKn3l33s) but the program keeps crashing and I keep getting "FileNotFoundError" errors. When I run pythonw testscript.py, I get a series of error messages. The last one and also the one that end my run in an error is ```python RELABELING Traceback (most recent call last): File "testscript.py", line 228, in DF = pd.read_hdf(file, "df_with_missing") File "/opt/anaconda3/envs/DLC-CPU/lib/python3.7/site-packages/pandas/io/pytables.py", line 387, in read_hdf raise FileNotFoundError(f"File {path_or_buf} does not exist") FileNotFoundError: File /Users/shawtylow/Desktop/DLCTest/DeepLabCut/examples/TEST-Alex-2021-02-04/labeled-data/reachingvideo1short/machinelabels-iter0.h5 does not exist ``` I also get "No video(s)" were found errors at other stages of this program but it doesn't seem to kill it. **How to Reproduce the problem** Steps to reproduce the behavior: 1. install anaconda 2. git clone deeplabcut 3. create the dlc-cpu environment 4. activate this environment 5. cd into deeplabcut/examples 6. run "pythonw testscript.py" 7. wait for error **Screenshots** Here is what my terminal output looks like right before crashing **Additional Context** It appears to me that testscript.py is responsible for creating all these files since they are not on the original GitHub. Am I correct in believing this? Also, the first thing to be missing is reachingvideo1short. That directory does not appear under labeled-data. Thanks so much!
